Values for the "Memento-Datetime" headers MUST be datetimes expressed according 
to the rfc1123-date construction rule of the BNF in ; 
they MUST be represented in Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).

However, in case a TimeMap wants to explicitly indicate in its response headers  
          for which Original Resource it is a TimeMap, 
          it MUST do so by including a HTTP "Link" header with the following characteristics:

